(\{ (\{ 6, 1 \}), (\{ "h1", "Garment Calculator" \}), (\{ "text", "So you've decided what you want to wear, but you aren't sure if it's appropriate or not. Here's a simple way to figure it out. Consider your rank, choose your fabric, choose your garment, and choose your color. Each of these have been assigned a number (see below). Calculate the sum of the numbers for the fabric, garment, and color. This total should be no more than one number more than the number corresponding to your rank*.\
\
\\r\\n\Note: This calculator is for an individual garment, not an entire outfit.\\\r\\n\
\
\\r\\n\\Formula: ([fabric] + [color] + [extras] + [garment rating] ) \≤ ([rank] + 1)\\\
\\r\\n\
\\r\\n\
\\r\\nSo let's calculate the value of a navy blue (dark blue) twill burgundian with twill lace.\
\
\\r\\nfabric value: 2\
\\r\\ncolor value: 3\
\\r\\nextras value: 2\
\\r\\ngarment rating value: 2\
\
\\r\\n2 + 3 + 2 + 2 = 9\
\
\\r\\nNow let's take that value, 9, and add 1 to get a grand total of 10. Apply this grand total number to rank values. Unless you are gentry or higher, you shouldn't be wearing it! However, by no means are you going to be forced to wear what would be appropriate, but you'd look out of place--consider it like wearing a tuxedo at a fast food restaurant." \}), (\{ "text", "\
